.TH "of_dma_find_controller" 9 "of_dma_find_controller" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
of_dma_find_controller \- Get a DMA controller in DT DMA helpers list
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct of_dma *" of_dma_find_controller
.BI "(struct of_phandle_args *dma_spec "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dma_spec" 12
pointer to DMA specifier as found in the device tree
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Finds a DMA controller with matching device node and number for dma cells
in a list of registered DMA controllers. If a match is found a valid pointer
to the DMA data stored is retuned. A NULL pointer is returned if no match is
found.
